18/12/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Jovan Trpenovski was appointed the new chairman of the Anticorruption Commission Wednesday (17 December). 
He will replace Slagjana Taseva, whose one-year mandate has expired. 
Presenting the commission's report for 2003 to the press, Taseva admitted that much work remains to be done.
Also Wednesday, Erhard Busek, the special co-ordinator of the Stability Pact for South Eastern Europe, arrived on a three-day visit to Skopje. 
He met first with Deputy Prime Minister Radmila Sekerinska to discuss Macedonia's activities within the Pact and progress in implementing the Ohrid Peace Accord. 
He also will meet with President Boris Trajkovski and Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 18/12/03; MIA, A1 TV - 17/12/03)
